author: Zoie O'Brien
title: Storm Doris kills woman in Wolverhampton - one dead after debris falls | UK | News | Express.co.uk
text:
BREAKING: Woman dead after Storm Doris RIPS OFF shop front in Wolverhampton BREAKING: Woman dead after Storm Doris RIPS OFF shop front in Wolverhampton STORM Doris has left one woman dead in Wolverhampton after being hit with falling debris when high winds ripped off a shop front. PUBLISHED: 12:53, Thu, Feb 23, 2017 | UPDATED: 13:36, Thu, Feb 23, 2017 
Police have sealed off part of Wolverhampton City centre after rushing to the scene. 
Officers received 15 calls for help, at around 11:43am this morning. 
The ambulance service said they were dealing with a "serious incident" in the centre. 
West Midlands Ambulance Service spokesman Murray MacGregor said: “On arrival, crews found a woman who had suffered very serious head injuries. 
“Sadly, it quickly became apparent that there was nothing that could be done to save her and she was confirmed dead at the scene.” Storm Dories leaves ONE dead Thu, February 23, 2017
